1
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:23,607
We have seen a star in the east.

2
00:00:25,359 --> 00:00:30,030
It told us
the Son of God is born.

3
00:01:02,104 --> 00:01:05,899
Nativity Play/Sermon/Dinner

4
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:08,902
The Lord Jesus
was laid in a manger...

5
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:12,656
...to bring salvation
to the souls of those...

6
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:15,868
...with no place of their own.

7
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:19,329
Nothing is harder
than to have no place...

8
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:23,417
...but many are those
without one.

9
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:24,877
Tell me about it!

10
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:28,338
In their solitude,
they long for someone who will say:

11
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:29,798
"I want you to be here."

12
00:01:30,048 --> 00:01:31,425
Not me, thanks.

13
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:32,718
Be quiet!

14
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:38,473
Jesus was born to offer those alone
a place in which to be alive!

15
00:01:41,393 --> 00:01:43,687
"Joy to the world,
the food has come."

16
00:01:43,896 --> 00:01:46,440
Gin! It's "the Lord has come"!

17
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:48,817
You don't know much, do you?

18
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:51,528
More than some faggot.

19
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:54,948
I am a mistake made by God.

20
00:01:55,199 --> 00:01:57,784
In my heart, I am a woman.

21
00:01:57,993 --> 00:01:59,828
Women can have children.

22
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:03,790
What if a miracle like
the Virgin Mary getting pregnant...

23
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:06,627
...was to happen to a homo?

24
00:02:07,169 --> 00:02:13,300
Better give me a little extra.
After all, I'm eating for two.

25
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,243
Serves you right!

26
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:43,455
Miyuki!

27
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,667
Time to eat!

28
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:51,755
Miyuki!

29
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:55,342
Close your legs!
Act like you were a woman.

30
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:56,677
I am a woman.

31
00:02:56,844 --> 00:02:59,721
And it's a waste
to spill food like that.

32
00:03:01,223 --> 00:03:03,433
Don't just gobble your bread.

33
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:08,272
Eat it with love for the people
who made and brought it here.

34
00:03:08,564 --> 00:03:12,651
I hate that Bible-thumping.
You're just like Akiko.

35
00:03:12,943 --> 00:03:14,319
Who's Akiko?

36
00:03:15,988 --> 00:03:17,072
My old lady.

37
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:18,031
Well!

38
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:20,117
Don't call your mother that.

39
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,536
Eat shit, you old fart.

40
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:25,038
"Shit" I'll take, but "fart" I won't!

41
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:27,040
That hurts! You old...

42
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:29,251
..."bag lady."

43
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:34,464
You peep pretty loud for a chick
that can't even find its own worms.

44
00:03:34,631 --> 00:03:37,968
Should a burden on society
like you be talking?

45
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:42,139
You're a burden on us.
What does that make you?

46
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:45,893
The kettle the pot's calling black!

47
00:03:47,477 --> 00:03:49,104
You mouthy brat!

48
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:53,483
Can't you at least get along
at Christmas?

49
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:57,112
Oh, yes....
Miyuki, I got you a present.

50
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:01,783
They're gone!

51
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,162
A whole set of
"World Literature for Children."

52
00:04:05,329 --> 00:04:07,748
Why would I need that?!

53
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:09,666
Hana looked hard for those!

54
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:13,879
Even a homeless teenage runaway
needs a Christmas present!

55
00:04:15,297 --> 00:04:17,382
I choose not to go home.

56
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:21,011
Six months on the street
means you don't have a home.

57
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:23,931
I can go home
any time I want to.

58
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:27,684
It's the ones who say that
who never do.

59
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,937
Speak for yourself,
you old geezer!

60
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:33,273
What are you doing
to Dostoevsky?!

61
00:04:34,191 --> 00:04:37,653
I won't take that,
today of all days!

62
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:42,115
Not even my father
ever hit me!

63
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:45,953
So I'll do it for him!

64
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,292
Grow up, will you?!

65
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:54,795
Don't hurt yourselves.

66
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,214
Show more respect, kid!

67
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:58,966
I'm not a kid!

68
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:01,635
With little tits like these?

69
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,887
You filthy old pervert!
That's harassment!

70
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,056
Will you two stop!

71
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:10,060
Huh?

72
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:31,039
It's been...

73
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:32,583
...abandoned.

74
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:35,294
There, there, there.

75
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:40,424
Care for this child.

76
00:05:42,885 --> 00:05:44,595
What a world!

77
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:46,013
Oh, man!

78
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:50,601
Oh, my! You're a little girl.
I wonder what your name is.

79
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,394
"John Doe."

80
00:05:52,561 --> 00:05:54,730
She's a girl, I said!
He's so rude!

81
00:05:55,564 --> 00:06:01,111
How old was I when I started
living like this? Thirty-something?

82
00:06:03,113 --> 00:06:07,075
I still thought
that I was better off...

83
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,745
...than a child with no home.

84
00:06:17,461 --> 00:06:21,798
There, there, now! We'll take you
somewhere warm.

85
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:26,720
The cop shop's that way!

86
00:06:28,514 --> 00:06:31,058
This is a Christmas present
from God!

87
00:06:31,225 --> 00:06:33,894
She's our baby!

88
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:35,062
Huh?

89
