98
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,114
Sorry!

99
00:07:27,531 --> 00:07:30,450
What do you mean,
take her with us?

100
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:33,203
I'm just doing God's will.

101
00:07:33,495 --> 00:07:35,372
Her parents might come back.

102
00:07:35,706 --> 00:07:39,126
What parent would leave
a child out in this cold?!

103
00:07:39,334 --> 00:07:42,004
That's a devil, not a parent!

104
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:48,302
Kiyoko wanted us
to find her.

105
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,595
"Kiyoko"?

106
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:52,306
"Kiyoko"? Why "Kiyoko"?!

107
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:56,643
From kiyo, "pure,"
on this purest of nights.

108
00:07:57,269 --> 00:07:58,145
How tacky!

109
00:07:58,312 --> 00:08:00,480
Kiyoko's a fine name!

110
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,983
Did you have
a girlfriend named that?

111
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,484
Idiot!

112
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:09,656
Look, we can't just name her!
She's not a puppy or a kitten!

113
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,325
So I'm taking her home.

114
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:12,826
To a cardboard box?

115
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:14,661
There's no room!

116
00:08:14,912 --> 00:08:20,000
This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance!
Let me feel like a mother!

117
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:24,713
A haiku:

118
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:31,595
"A little baby / powdery snow
on its cheeks / on this holy night. "

119
00:08:31,762 --> 00:08:35,682
Directed by
Satoshi Kon

120
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:49,279
Peek-a-boo!

121
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,534
Oh, dear! Tell me what's wrong!

122
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,285
Shut up!

123
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,123
Hey!

124
00:09:00,332 --> 00:09:04,920
I know, I know, he's not your mommy.
He's just a homeless homo.

125
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,798
Don't say that
in front of her!

126
00:09:08,006 --> 00:09:11,677
A baby crying around here
will sound weird!

127
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:15,138
We're going to take you
to the police soon, okay?

128
00:09:15,347 --> 00:09:17,683
You're not going anywhere,
are you?

129
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:20,519
Idiot! We're taking
her to the police!

130
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:22,813
Don't shout
or she'll never shut up!

131
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:26,400
Why won't you stop crying?
Are you hungry?

132
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:27,484
There, there!

133
00:09:27,693 --> 00:09:30,112
Maybe she's sick.

134
00:09:43,834 --> 00:09:47,504
Tomorrow....
I promise I'll take her then.

135
00:09:48,672 --> 00:09:53,177
Christmas should be
the happiest day of the year.

136
00:09:53,385 --> 00:09:56,763
If we take her in now, it'll always be
the worst day of her life!

137
00:09:58,473 --> 00:09:59,558
Maybe...

138
00:10:00,309 --> 00:10:02,186
...she needs a diaper.

139
00:10:12,196 --> 00:10:13,780
Hana, boil some water.

140
00:10:14,239 --> 00:10:15,616
I'll make some milk.

141
00:10:15,908 --> 00:10:18,160
Hey! Whose side are you on?!

142
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:22,789
Go buy some water!
My angel isn't drinking from the tap!

143
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,791
Why me?

144
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:30,797
Where does a bum get off telling me
"Them that works eats"?

145
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:37,554
Just for tonight, remember.
Tomorrow we take her to the police.

146
00:10:39,932 --> 00:10:43,936
So "no man is an island"
after all, huh?

147
00:10:48,106 --> 00:10:50,192
You're buying water?!

148
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:53,070
A Christmas miracle.

149
00:10:53,612 --> 00:10:55,697
What a haul!

150
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:04,498
Watch where you're going, brat!

151
00:11:04,665 --> 00:11:06,500
You watch where you're going!

152
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:12,631
I was married once.

153
00:11:12,965 --> 00:11:14,424
With a child?

154
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:18,512
No, don't tell me!
I don't want to hear this!

155
00:11:20,097 --> 00:11:23,350
You never forget
for one second.

156
00:11:23,517 --> 00:11:27,938
A child's the only thing
you hold dearer than life itself.

157
00:11:29,439 --> 00:11:30,732
A boy?

158
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:32,442
No.

159
00:11:36,947 --> 00:11:38,282
Bullshit!

160
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:40,450
Come on! Give it back!

161
00:11:40,784 --> 00:11:45,038
Hey, you're the girl
who hangs out with Gin.

162
00:11:45,247 --> 00:11:46,874
Get out of here, will you?

163
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,585
We don't want Gin after us.

164
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:51,545
Why not?

165
00:11:51,712 --> 00:11:55,132
You're the light of his life,
that's why not!

166
00:11:55,674 --> 00:12:00,804
There's not much light
in a cardboard box.

167
00:12:01,096 --> 00:12:03,265
Let me have this book.

168
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:07,811
How old?

169
00:12:07,978 --> 00:12:10,230
Twenty-one, I think.

170
00:12:10,689 --> 00:12:14,818
Five or six years older
than Miyuki, I guess.

171
00:12:15,027 --> 00:12:16,820
That old?

172
00:12:16,987 --> 00:12:19,406
If she was alive.

173
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:25,621
When I was 20 I got a girl pregnant,
and we got married.

174
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:28,123
I was in heaven.

175
00:12:28,499 --> 00:12:32,336
You could have poked me in the eye
and I'd have just smiled at you.

176
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:38,425
But my daughter got sick,
and the medical bills were huge.

177
00:12:38,634 --> 00:12:43,263
I was something of
a bicycle racer then.

178
00:12:43,889 --> 00:12:47,518
I needed money.
There was this race....

179
00:12:47,726 --> 00:12:48,936
You threw it?

180
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:55,234
A punk I knew
had this scheme.

181
00:12:55,400 --> 00:13:01,281
They found out, I got kicked out
of racing, and my girl died.

182
00:13:01,573 --> 00:13:04,701
I just didn't feel
like working anymore.

183
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:08,038
And then my wife
followed my daughter.

184
00:13:08,205 --> 00:13:09,289
Oh, no!

185
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:13,168
That's how you get to be
a man like me.

186
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:16,880
I didn't want to hear that!
I hate sad stories!

187
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:20,259
It's freezing!

188
00:13:23,887 --> 00:13:25,138
You're used to this.

189
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:26,515
Kind of.

190
00:13:26,682 --> 00:13:29,393
I'll give her the milk.

191
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,229
Dreams do come true.

192
00:13:32,396 --> 00:13:37,150
I always dreamed of being
the mother of a little girl.

193
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:39,570
A nice, warm house,
a pretty daughter.

194
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:42,406
Even if my husband
was no good...

195
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:45,576
...I would accept dire poverty
as long as I had my child.

196
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:47,786
Feed the poor kid!

197
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:54,668
You're so pretty.

198
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:59,214
The prettiest little girl
in the world.

199
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:25,741
What do you want?!

200
00:14:26,241 --> 00:14:27,534
They're gone.

201
00:14:30,829 --> 00:14:32,956
Santa Claus, maybe?

202
00:14:33,207 --> 00:14:36,293
"Uncle Bag" and the baby
are gone.

203
00:14:36,460 --> 00:14:39,254
What's that faggot
thinking about?!

204
00:14:42,049 --> 00:14:44,551
Man, he's got big feet!

205
00:14:44,718 --> 00:14:47,054
You can't have feet fixed.

206
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:05,989
Are you taking her back?

207
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,826
There's probably an APB
out on her.

208
00:15:10,202 --> 00:15:11,745
And for you.

209
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:12,663
I doubt it.

210
00:15:13,705 --> 00:15:17,000
An arrest warrant, maybe.

211
00:15:18,377 --> 00:15:21,505
Her parents are probably
sorry about this now.

212
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:24,049
So let's take her to the police.

213
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:29,012
A baby's always
better off with its real mother.

214
00:15:29,221 --> 00:15:31,014
Not necessarily.

215
00:15:32,891 --> 00:15:35,477
Sometimes a
foster mother's better.

216
00:15:35,686 --> 00:15:38,021
-What?!
-Don't be stupid.

217
00:15:38,814 --> 00:15:42,025
I never knew
my real mother.

218
00:15:44,027 --> 00:15:48,657
But I'll bet if she saw me now,
she'd flip.

219
00:15:49,992 --> 00:15:52,870
How can someone homeless
raise a child?

220
00:15:53,036 --> 00:15:55,539
I know, I know!

221
00:15:56,582 --> 00:16:00,294
I don't want her shunted
from one foster home to another...

222
00:16:00,586 --> 00:16:02,754
...without even one memory...

223
00:16:02,963 --> 00:16:05,174
...of ever having been loved.

224
00:16:05,507 --> 00:16:08,886
You don't have to be a foundling
to feel that.

225
00:16:09,386 --> 00:16:11,555
They must have had reasons.

226
00:16:11,763 --> 00:16:14,558
Nothing should make you
abandon a child!

227
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:21,148
That means you've taken love
and tossed it away, like trash.

228
00:16:22,608 --> 00:16:25,569
Yeah, but what can we
do about it?

229
00:16:26,278 --> 00:16:27,696
Find her mother.

230
00:16:29,907 --> 00:16:32,951
And ask why she abandoned
her baby.

231
00:16:34,328 --> 00:16:36,788
If she can make me understand...

232
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:40,292
...I'll forgive her,
and my mother too.

233
00:16:41,126 --> 00:16:43,212
Find her?

234
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:45,047
How?

235
00:16:49,134 --> 00:16:51,094
We'll have to pay again.

236
00:16:51,637 --> 00:16:54,765
This is an expensive year-end!

237
00:16:55,098 --> 00:16:57,226
What if we find another baby?

238
00:16:57,392 --> 00:16:59,937
They don't toss them out in twos.

239
00:17:11,156 --> 00:17:12,950
Another key!

240
00:17:13,158 --> 00:17:17,120
Look at these panties.
You'd catch cold in them!

241
00:17:17,788 --> 00:17:20,332
Are they the ones?

242
00:17:23,836 --> 00:17:25,879
Are these your folks?

243
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:28,215
Look, business cards.

244
00:17:35,681 --> 00:17:39,142
A hostess club
won't be open at this hour!

245
00:17:39,601 --> 00:17:41,979
We've got some walking to do.

246
00:17:42,145 --> 00:17:44,398
You've gotta be kidding!

247
00:17:47,693 --> 00:17:49,653
He was eating for two!

248
00:18:02,875 --> 00:18:08,505
But why pack like you're off on a trip
and then abandon a baby?

249
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:12,301
Maybe it was one last trip
they were taking.

250
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:13,635
A family suicide?!

251
00:18:15,262 --> 00:18:16,597
Then what do we do?

252
00:18:17,097 --> 00:18:19,224
We can't search the next world!

253
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:20,893
Shh!

254
00:18:27,024 --> 00:18:30,068
We apologize for
any inconvenience.

255
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:34,823
Trains will be delayed due
to heavy snowfall.

256
00:18:35,574 --> 00:18:37,075
It's so hot in here!

257
00:18:37,284 --> 00:18:38,994
What a stink!

258
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:42,539
Have you bathed lately?

259
00:18:43,248 --> 00:18:45,125
No. Or washed my clothes.

260
00:18:45,292 --> 00:18:47,002
How embarrassing!

